fields.value: Monitoring Corruption: Evidence from a Field Experiment in Indonesia

dsDescriptionValue.value: This is the raw data that is used for "Monitoring Corruption: Evidence from a Field Experiment in Indonesia." The data contains a household survey, key informant survey, meeting surveys, and an engineering road survey.

publicationCitation.value: Benjamin A. Olken, "Monitoring Corruption: Evidence from a Field Experiment in Indonesia," Journal of Political Economy 115, no. 2 (April 2007): 200-249.

fields.value: Subject: STANDARD DEPOSIT TERMS 1.0  Type: DATAPASS:TERMS:STANDARD:1.0  Notes: This study was deposited under the of the Data-PASS standard deposit terms. A copy of the usage agreement is included in the file section of this study.;

otherGeographicCoverage.value: East Java and Central Java Province
